<div class="section_title">Honoree Benefits</div>
<span class="text">
<UL>
<LI><SPAN class=subhead>Added Honoree Benefit!</SPAN> The highly anticipated Innovations 2005 honoree announcement will be made at the New York International CES Press Preview, attended by the industry's media elite, on November 10, 2004. Make sure your company name and winning products are included in the breaking news headlines. RSVP to attend the FREE Innovations Lounge in a luxury suite at the upscale Mandarin Hotel, where honorees will: 
<UL>
<LI>Mingle with the media attending the Press Preview, with award presentation photo opportunities in the Innovations Lounge </LI>
<LI>Attend the press conference in the luxurious Lotus Room of the Mandarin Hotel, where the Best of Innovations 2005 honorees will be publicly announced for the first time. </LI>
<LI>Party with the press at an exclusive reception at one of Manhattanâ€™s hottest new restaurants, the Stone Rose.</LI></UL><BR><SPAN class=text_colored>Gain a spotlight for your product and brand in one of the most talked about venues of the International CES. Attendees and journalists will want to meet you. RSVP to <A href="mailto:jilly@ce.org?subject=RSVP to NYC Press Event" target=_blank>Jamie Lilly</A> or (703) 907-7650.</SPAN> <BR><BR></LI>
<LI>Earn the right to place the coveted Innovations logo on your product's packaging and advertising.&nbsp; </LI>
<LI>Receive additional exposure in the prestigious Innovations Plus area located in CES Central Plaza at the 2005 International CES.&nbsp; </LI>
<LI>Demonstrate your product during <A href="http://www.cesweb.org/exhibitors/promotions/press.asp?id=1#658" target=_blank>CES Unveiled, the Official Press Event for the International CES</A>. For more details, contact <A href="mailto:rstrowger@ce.org" target=_blank>Ryan Strowger</A>&nbsp; or call (703) 907 7679. </LI>
<LI>Showcase your product design or company ad on click panels on display in the IDSA Designer Gallery, located inside the Innovations Showcase (for IDSA members only). </LI>
<LI>Participate in the live radio broadcast of <EM>Into Tomorrow with Dave Graveline</EM> in the New-to-Market area of Innovations Plus.<BR><IMG height=40 src="/print/images/partners/graveline.gif" width=120 vspace=6><BR>This nationally syndicated consumer electronics radio program will launch its 10th&nbsp;season at the 2005 International CES. Host Dave Graveline will interview CEOs, presidents and senior executives from the hottest companies exhibiting at CES, producing three entire programs (9 hours of programming), live from the International CES show floor.<BR><SPAN class=text_colored>Reserve your International CES broadcast airtime now. Call now to pitch your story. Contact Fausto C&oacute;rdova, Producer, (305) 824-9000 ext. 10, <A href="mailto:fausto@graveline.com" target=_blank>fausto@graveline.com</A>.<BR><BR></SPAN> </LI>
<LI>Display signage in your booth acknowledging your Innovations honoree status. </LI>
<LI>Receive a beautiful Innovations 2005 award to display in your booth at the 2005 International CES or in your trophy case. </LI>
<LI>Receive a listing in the Innovations 2005 on-site directory. </LI>
<LI>Receive the Innovations icon published next to your company listing in the Official CES Show Directory (for official International CES exhibitors only). </LI>
<LI>Gain industry-wide recognition and media attention through a CEA press release. Plus, garner the attention of key industry journalists and retailers who visit the Innovations honoree displays. </LI>
<LI>Get exposure on the official website, <A href="http://www.cesweb.org/Innovations">www.CESweb.org/Innovations</A>, where the Innovations pages are among the most visited pages! Benefit from inclusion in <A href="http://www.idsa.org/" target=_blank>IDSAâ€™s</A> quarterly design publication.</LI></UL></SPAN>
</span>
